            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@lewis6991 on matrix on the bisected commit:\n\n> We wanted richer types for Lua which the PR added but needed to maintain compat for rpc types without adding the new ones. Normalizing ArrayOf to Array was the easiest route since it stood out.\n> Basically it was done just to appease the tests.\n\nWhich is fair enough. Richer Lua types would eventually allow richer rpc types too.\n\nRegarding this issue, for me this just means that I need to add few manual overrides to my API generation, which is no biggie (I should've been more proactive with my API generation as neovim progressed forward).",
