            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Before 0.12.0, I could see from `--api-info` that, e.g., `nvim_list_runtime_paths` returns an Array of `String`s such that I could generate a Swift function which returns `[String]`. Now, the `--api-info` call returns *only* `Array`, not `Array(String)` or similar. Shouldn't the API info call return that information?",
