        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Overlaps with:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19918 \n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/18750 \n\nRather than introduce a bespoke type DSL, I would suggest we do either or both of the following:\n\n1. ship a builtin luadoc / emmylua parser so that downstream can consume `runtime/lua/vim/_meta/api.lua` and similar lua \"types\" files to get structured type info.\n    - for convenience we can also ship a wrapper (maybe `get_api_info()` is the wrapper) so that it's easy to get a structure instead of fiddling with parser details.\n2. ship existing metadata structures such as `src/nvim/eval.lua`.\n    - currently we don't an equivalent file for API types, we just need to generate one from `gen_vimdoc.lua`.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-05T14:45:40Z",
